# Everything is excluded by default — Docker only ever needs the staged
# Play distribution that `sbt stage` produces (and the Dockerfile itself).
# Source, tests, fixtures, build caches, and .git are pure noise for the
# runtime image and bloat the build-context upload to Fly's remote builder.
*

# Whitelist the staged Play distribution. The GitHub Actions deploy job
# places it at `stage/` (not its native `target/universal/stage` path)
# precisely so this exclusion can be a single top-level whitelist — Docker's
# `.dockerignore` doesn't reliably re-include a deep path whose parents are
# ignored by `*`.
!stage
!stage/**

# The Dockerfile is part of the build context (always sent), but listing
# it here explicitly survives any future top-level pattern change.
!Dockerfile
